  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nNode with config `\"SnapSync\": true` but without `\"FastSync\": true` is not starting sync.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Run client with \"SnapSync\": true instead of \"FastSync\": true\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nFastSync should be true always when SnapSync is true, as expected in https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/pull/4113\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nIn PR above FastSync value is overriden only here:\r\nhttps://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/blob/c1407f6b676bbef8c59dfd7c3a922cecbaece741/src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Synchronization/ParallelSync/MultiSyncModeSelector.cs#L51\r\n\r\nE.g. here we are using again not overriden config:\r\nhttps://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/blob/c1407f6b676bbef8c59dfd7c3a922cecbaece741/src/Nethermind/Nethermind.Synchronization/ParallelSync/MultiSyncModeSelector.cs#L53\r\n\r\nAs we are using fast sync config in other places than MultiModeSYncSelector too, I think we should override fast sync config value earlier, before it is used anywhere",
